						               													<description>Take me out to the ball game!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Nick's Finger Baseball is a free, two player game of strategy and outwitting. Playing the role of the captains of two baseball teams, both endeavor to lead their team to victory.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Over the course of 9 innings, there are a large number of turns. In each turn, each player simultaneously reveals their strategy for that part of the game. The player whose team is on offence reveals a number between 0 and 4, trying to reveal a high number... or are they? For they are also trying to avoid revealing one of the 2 numbers the defense revealed at that time, as revealing those spells disaster, which just gets worse the higher the number is! Do you shoot for high numbers and hope the defense isn't there, or try to sneak a lower number past them? As the defense, do you block the high numbers to stop power plays, or aim lower and stop sneaky plays?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Those are the types of choices you have to make in Nick's Finger Baseball, a battle of wits for 2 players!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
